            "chars": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>LD.XVIII.R8</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Mr Rugg, and &ldquo;deferring to the opinion of Society&rdquo;</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-38c9ef38-7fff-95d6-8729-c462159c4fba\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The chapter uses the phrase &ldquo;Public Opinion&rdquo; rather than &ldquo;Society&rdquo;: &ldquo;&lsquo;Might it not be advisable, sir,&rsquo; said Mr. Rugg, more coaxingly yet, &lsquo;now to make, at last and after all, a trifling concession to public opinion?&rsquo;&rdquo; (LD 719).</p>"
